Description: Corner-fragment of a model-building carved in limestone; courses of brick indicated by incised lines.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir William Matthew Flinders Petrie (probably)
Curator's comments: This find is probably mentioned in Petrie journal 1884-1885: "A piece of a model house in limestone & a corner showing two windows & two ventilators, & all lined over to show courses of brick, with stone lintels to the windows." Compare with BM, AES 2462 and other models in Cairo Museum
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XVIII, no. 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (CF.2)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (Committee of)
